    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Agreed, this would be a helpful flag, IMO this request is also a \"good first issue\" candidate.\r\n\r\nIn the meantime you can give geth more file handles for network sockets via `prlimit`, e.g. something like:\r\n\r\n```\r\n# define $GETH_PID somehow (`pgrep geth`, etc.)\r\nprlimit -p $GETH_PID --nofile=4096:4096\r\n# confirm \r\ncat /proc/${GETH_PID}/limits\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf you do this a couple seconds after `geth` starts, it'll continue to use half of the original 2048 handles for leveldb, while the rest added via `prlimit` are available for socket connections.",
